Photographer, researcher, educator, conservationist, filmmaker, author, and explorer Jacques Cousteau has left a legacy that continues to inspire us all. When he and his team boarded Calypso in 1951, they had no idea they would soon find the devastating effects of pollution and over- exploitation. From here, Calypso would go on to serve as ground zero for the development of underwater housing equipment and technology. He wanted to be able to move more freely underwater and longer which is what started the innovation of Aqualung, or better known as Scuba. He and his crew would go on to explore and film the world around them; in return they would use this to not only further their research, but to educate others and spread the message of protection.-‚Äúpeople protect what they love‚Äù. ‚Å†
