ÔøΩIs it carving pumpkins for Halloween or going on long walks to feel the crisp air? Perhaps it‚Äôs spending time with loved ones over a hearty meal.ÔøΩ But the main hallmark of autumn is the dramatic transformation taking place in nature. Leaves slowly change from bright green to yellow, brown, orange or red, before floating gracefully to the ground. But their lifecycle doesn‚Äôt end there. Not unlike the whale fall, they support biodiversity in the afterlife by becoming nourishing leaf litter.

